<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="cond"
>cond</a></h2>

<p>Most of the navigation functions accept a condition as an optional argument The first element (or all elements for <code><a href="/perldoc?children" class="podlinkpod"
>children</a> </code> or <code><a href="/perldoc?ancestors" class="podlinkpod"
>ancestors</a> </code>) that passes the condition is returned.</p>

<p>The condition is a single step of an XPath expression using the XPath subset defined by <code><a href="/perldoc?get_xpath" class="podlinkpod"
>get_xpath</a></code>. Additional conditions are:</p>

<p>The condition can be</p>

<dl>
<dt><a name='ELT'></a><a name="#ELT"
>#ELT</a></dt>

<dd>
<p>return a &#34;real&#34; element (not a PCDATA, CDATA, comment or pi element)</p>

